THE FIRST day of schoolwas a tragedy for two schools in Ntuzuma, KZN.Four pupils from Sivananda Technical High and Sibonelo High schools died and 16 kids were injured when their taxi collided with a bus yesterday. One passenger in the bus was injured.Paramedics and cops said the taxi carrying 21 pupils was allegedly speeding when it tried to overtake a car and collided with the bus.Nkosinathi Mjwara (37) told Daily Sun he was battling to accept the death of his daughter, Thabisile (16).He said his son Benni (13) was airlifted to hospital after sustaining critical injuries.&ldquo;I can see Thabisile is not breathing, but it is hard for me to accept she is dead.&rdquo; KZN Emergency Medical Services spokesman Robert McKenzie said the injured were taken to hospitals in the area.KZN co-operative governance MEC Nomusa Dube-Ncube couldn&rsquo;t hold back her tears when she arrived at the scene.&ldquo;I was happy to be visiting schools around the province in the morning, but now I am heartbroken,&rdquo; she said.She sent her condolences to the affected families and schools and urged motorists to drive responsibly.Sicelo Khuzwayo, spokesman for KZN education MEC Mthandeni Dlungwana, said:&ldquo;The MEC extends his condolences to the affected schools, pupils and families.&rdquo;KZN police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbhele confirmed that four people had died in the accident.&ldquo;A case of culpable homicide was opened at Ntuzuma police station for further investigation. &ldquo;The cause of the accident is still being investigated.&rdquo;